{"id": "EUVD-2025-5983", "enisaUuid": "3affd854-00f1-3f89-bf3b-d0506e1fb812", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nblock: mark GFP_NOIO around sysfs ->store()\n\nsysfs ->store is called with queue freezed, meantime we have several\n->store() callbacks(update_nr_requests, wbt, scheduler) to allocate\nmemory with GFP_KERNEL which may run into direct reclaim code path,\nthen potential deadlock can be caused.\n\nFix the issue by marking NOIO around sysfs ->store()", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T21:32:17", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-28T03:30:13", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21817", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2566ce907e5d5db8a039647208e029ce559baa31", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7c0be4ead1f8f5f8be0803f347de0de81e3b8e1c"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21817", "GHSA-3f4p-8qj7-5fxp"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "11cd9acc-1500-3688-921b-0eba4fd93f50", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8985da5481562e96b95e94ed8e5cc9b6565eb82b <2566ce907e5d5db8a039647208e029ce559baa31"}, {"id": "1fab57b5-eaf7-3990-8fc4-30d05458d3cd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.3"}, {"id": "53e91d64-143f-33dd-9d49-eaaa10fec74b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <2566ce907e5d5db8a039647208e029ce559baa31"}, {"id": "67043ce5-82ec-37a2-8645-41ba13cf0163", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13.2 <6.13.3"}, {"id": "7d113517-6159-32a5-b01a-c1a4d95b38d4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14"}, {"id": "8167b0c6-dd8f-33a2-a9db-020126a03725", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c99f66e4084a62a2cc401c4704a84328aeddc9ec <7c0be4ead1f8f5f8be0803f347de0de81e3b8e1c"}, {"id": "a8e35c63-ac42-3d6b-a30d-ebe4012e85b5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <7c0be4ead1f8f5f8be0803f347de0de